# EJS Views & Bootstrap Rules

## Layout Parts
Shared partials live in `views/parts/` — always include them in this order:
1. `head.ejs` → `head-end.ejs`
2. `body.ejs` (navbar via `navigation.ejs`)
3. Page content
4. `body-end.ejs`

## Bootstrap Usage
- Use Bootstrap CDN (already included in `head.ejs`) — do not add a local copy.
- Cards for product listings, `list-group` for cart/order items.
- Use `btn btn-primary` / `btn btn-danger` for actions consistently.

## Forms
- Add-to-cart form is the shared partial `views/parts/add-to-cart.ejs` — reuse it, do not duplicate.
- Hidden `<input name="id">` carries the product id to `POST /cart`.
- All forms use `method="POST"`; no client-side fetch unless explicitly requested.
- Every POST form must include hidden `_csrf` with value from `csrfToken` local.

## Variable Contract
Each rendered view receives at minimum:
- `pageTitle` — used in `<title>` tag inside `head.ejs`
- `url` — used to highlight the active nav link in `navigation.ejs`
- `isLoggedIn` — controls nav item visibility
- `csrfToken` — required by forms to pass global CSRF middleware

## Do Not
- Do not add inline `<style>` blocks; use `public/css/*.css` instead.
- Do not introduce a JS framework (React, Vue) — views are server-rendered EJS only.

